setInitialLimit

void setInitialLimit(Integer initialLimit)
                     throws SQLException
Sets how many connections are created in the cache when it is created or reinitialized. When this property is set to an integer value greater than 0, creating or reinitializing the cache automatically creates the specified number of connections, filling the cache in advance of need.

Parameters:
initialLimit - the initialLimit to set Default: 0
Throws:
SQLException

getMaxLimit

                throws SQLException
Returns:

Throws:
SQLException

setMaxLimit

void setMaxLimit(Integer maxLimit)
                 throws SQLException
Sets the maximum number of cached Connections. The default value is Integer.MAX_VALUE, meaning that there is no limit enforced by the connection cache, so that the number of connections is limited only by the number of database sessions configured for the database.

Parameters:
maxLimit - the maxLimit to set
Throws:
SQLException
